OL,3,CPolls close for the Gorton and Denton
OL,4,Cby-election
OL,6,FThe former health minister was
OL,7,Fsuspended from the Labour Party in
OL,8,FFebruary 2025 over offensive Whatsapp
OL,9,Fmessages including antisemitic slights
OL,10,Fand jokes about a constituent being
OL,11,F"mown down" by a truck.
OL,13,FGwynne, who had been an MP since 2005,
OL,14,Fwon the most recent July 2024 general
OL,15,Felection with a majority of more than
OL,16,F13,000, having received 50.8% of the
OL,17,Fvote.
OL,19,FGorton and Denton by-election
